                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor(s); first line in the incipit of Texts I and III and first word in the incipit of Text II; the initial word of some sections of Text I (fols. 3r, 5r);  Trinitarian formula (or part of it); the words masqal (and its abbreviation) and ʾaganǝnt (fol. 27r); some words written interlineally (e.g., fol. 52v); elements of the punctuation signs and the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
